CatDescriptText: Thomas Reese, 365-1/2 Prince Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1958, pg. 3, with question: "Do you think that there will be an economic depression in near future like the one in the early thirties?" answer reads: "I think that there will be if there's no change soon. Yes, its my feeling that things are going to be pretty tough.  I'm afraid they will be rough."
